snippet.textDisplay: My dad about three years ago told me about Mac and I ignored him thinking that he was just another artist. Then after he passed I still didn't listen and I don't know why. But when circles came out and i thought "sure I'll listen" didn't think it would break me down after the third song. It was beautiful and then I listened to swimming and now I feel bad that I didn't listen to him while he was alive. But I am glad all of this was released or I would not be listening to his or I might not be here now typing this. Thanks Mac you help me stop cutting. Love you Mac

snippet.textDisplay: The hope Mac has given me throughout my teens and becoming a man is something special. We’re the same age, so I grew up right along beside him. Seemed like he was making songs especially for me. We had the same struggles and he gave me hope in my darkest times. To this day, if I’m feeling depressed, I throw on a random Mac Miller vinyl and escape it all... life can be so hard.  Man, we miss you Mac. Love you big guy!
